The paper focuses on understanding user behavior in Virtual Reality (VR) applications, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and graphics (cs.GR). The proposed method involves analyzing navigation patterns in 360-degree content, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the potential application of detecting disorders in medical applications, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR).
